Despite our political differences, I suddenly like Paul Ryan a lot better. Finally the Republican Party leaders are rebuking the atrocities that are coming out of Donald Trumps mouth. 

A few months ago I asked "Why are we will talking about Trump? This is ridiculous." and yet the conversations grew louder, more frequent, and more terrifying. I'd have never considered Paul Ryan a powerful orator before - it's tough to stand up against the oration power of President Obama - but this stands apart. 

According to the latest polls 19% of Republican voters favor Trump. That's one in five. One in ten americans. I trust the other 90% of Americans to not be racist, classist, sexist sheep who follow the loudest voice. I trust that Donald Trump will never be our elected president. But the things he says, and the ability he has to invoke violence and hatred toward fellow humans is scary and it's dangerous. I can only hope that leaders of the Republican Party (especially those not trying to win an election) continue to speak out with such passion and truth against the fascism that radiates throughout the Donald Trump campaign.
